
  Create work instruction for instrument and sub-assembly testing
  Coordinate PCBA tester development and supplier site deployment
  Support PCBA evaluation from alternative supplier
  Troubleshoot electronic part issues
  Update drawing and release ECR/ECO in Agile
  Set up and validate new tester
  Assist Engineers in problem-solving and troubleshooting

Role Requirements


  Diploma in Electrical Engineering or equivalent with minimum 2 years of experience in a manufacturing environment.
  Preferably with programming knowledge/experience (e.g. LabVIEW/C++/VB)
  Preferably with experience on product assembly and testing.
  Good analytical and problem-solving skills.
  Able to communicate with cross-functional levels.
  Able to work night shift
